# Privacy Policy for DebugLab: Code Editor & Learning

Last Updated: [DATE]

DebugLab: Code Editor & Learning ("DebugLab", "we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, and protected when you use our mobile application.

## Information We Collect

### Account Information

If you sign in using Google Sign-In, we may collect:

* Name
* Email address
* Profile picture (if provided by Google)

### Learning Data

To provide educational features, we may store:

* Learning progress
* Quiz scores
* Achievements and badges
* Bookmarks and favorites
* Saved coding projects
* App preferences and settings

### Device and Usage Information

We may automatically collect:

* Device type
* Operating system version
* App version
* Crash reports
* Diagnostic information
* Usage analytics

### Advertising Information

DebugLab may use Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect advertising-related identifiers and usage information as described in Google's Privacy Policy.

## How We Use Information

We use collected information to:

* Provide educational content and coding tools
* Save user progress
* Improve app performance
* Fix technical issues and crashes
* Personalize the learning experience
* Analyze feature usage
* Display relevant advertisements

## Third-Party Services

DebugLab may use the following third-party services:

* Firebase Authentication
* Firebase Firestore
* Firebase Analytics
* Firebase Crashlytics
* Google AdMob

These services may collect information according to their own privacy policies.

## Data Storage and Security

We take reasonable measures to protect user information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or misuse.

While we strive to protect your information, no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is completely secure.

## Children's Privacy

DebugLab is designed for students and learners.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age required by applicable laws without appropriate consent.

If you believe a child has provided personal information, please contact us and we will take appropriate action.

## Data Retention

We retain user data only as long as necessary to provide app functionality and comply with legal obligations.

Users may request deletion of their account data by contacting us.

## User Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the right to:

* Access your information
* Correct inaccurate information
* Request deletion of information
* Withdraw consent where applicable

Requests may be submitted through the contact information below.

